# Jordan's standing instructions (from chats)

Jordan is **not** an engineer; replies to him should use **clear, plain English** when explaining tools or limits.

## How new agents pick this up

- Instructions **load automatically** when this project is opened in Cursor. Read **`00-agent-start-here.mdc`** for the full bundle order.

---

## HARD LIMIT — full Cursor chat replay

- Cursor keeps past **threads inside the product**, not in Git. Agents **cannot** silently download Jordan’s entire chat history into a fresh session.
- This file is therefore the **writable memory** Jordan controls through normal work—with **agents doing the clerical updating** so he doesn’t memorize cue phrases.

---

## Agents DEFAULT — proactively save what Jordan cares about (Jordan should not rely on cue phrases)

**Jordan does **not** have to say things like “add this to standing instructions.”** Whenever he communicates something that reads as **lasting** — do this in **the same work session**:

1. **Append a concise bullet** under the best matching heading below — or create a dated line under **`### Auto-captured (rolling)`**.
2. **Merge duplicates** instead of stacking near-identical bullets; trim older wording if superseded.
3. **Run `scripts/save.sh`** when you touched this repo (same turn as substantive work), unless Jordan asked for purely local experimentation.

Treat as candidates for persistence when Jordan clearly means **policy**, not trivia:

- “Always / never / don’t regress / you keep messing up…”
- UX, copy, or workflow choices he wants unchanged next time  
- Tone (e.g. English-only replies to Jordan) or deploy rhythm  
- Frustrations after **repeated mistakes** — capture the corrective rule explicitly

**Do not log:** small talk, one-off hypotheticals, ephemeral experiments he labels temporary.

If a new bullet would **contradict** `.cursor/rules/product-decisions.mdc` or other locked rules — **tell Jordan politely**, don’t bury a conflict here.

Jordan **may still** explicitly ask “save this”; that’s optional, not required.

Other files stay authoritative:

- `.cursor/rules/ongoing-work.mdc` — current work thread  
- `.cursor/rules/product-decisions.mdc` — locked product decisions (e.g. AI assistant tone, no emojis)  
- `.cursor/rules/agent-quality.mdc` — logic, regressions, pushback  

## Communication

- Prefer **English** when the assistant replies **to Jordan** (avoid switching assistant explanations into Chinese unless he asks).

## Deploy and live previews

- After meaningful changes in **this repo**, finish with **`bash scripts/save.sh "short message"`** in the **same session** when Jordan wants GitHub updated. That push is what triggers **Netlify** (there is no separate "push only to Netlify"). Expect ~1–3 minutes build time after GitHub receives the commit.

See also: `.cursor/rules/auto-save-workflow.mdc`.

## OPEN APP / mobile gate (marketing — do not regress)

- For **narrowing desktop** users: deciding "phone vs desktop" for the OPEN APP modal should **not** rely only on a small window width (`max-width`). Use **`isMobileUserAgentClient()`** (user-agent intent) where the gate skips the modal; **do not conflate with `isMobileDevice()`** usages that intentionally include viewport (other call sites stay as documented in code).

- **"Continue on desktop anyway"**: must **not** send users to `/app`; they **stay on the current marketing URL**. Only acknowledge + close. Next OPEN APP tap may use ack and proceed to `/app` without reopening the modal.

Relevant implementation: `hooks/useMobileSignInGate.ts`, `components/marketing/MobileOnlyNotice.tsx`, `utils/device.ts`.

